[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Retrieve source documents.** Pull the notes that are in scope. For a current-admission summary, that's the notes from this encounter. For a longitudinal summary, it's a broader pull bounded by the time window the clinician specified. Retrieval should also include structured data relevant to the summary scope: medication lists, problem lists, allergies, recent labs, recent imaging reads. Structured data is easier to summarize faithfully than prose. Critically, retrieval must filter out notes from restricted data categories (42 CFR Part 2 substance-use-treatment records, HIV-related content, adolescent confidential notes, genetic test results) unless the requesting user has a specific disclosure consent on file. Access control is enforced at the retrieval layer, not bolted on downstream.
